01:27:44.620 --> 01:27:50.570
But I have savings, and IT workers
get extra unemployment benefits.


1039
01:27:50.780 --> 01:27:53.070
I'll just take it as a break.

1040
01:27:53.530 --> 01:27:54.620
That's good.

1041
01:27:56.490 --> 01:27:57.870
Hello.

1042
01:27:58.620 --> 01:28:00.450
- Hot, isn't it?
- It is.


1043
01:28:00.660 --> 01:28:03.570
- Yu had fun at your home.
- I'm glad.


1044
01:28:03.740 --> 01:28:06.740
Hitomi can come play anytime, too.

1045
01:28:08.120 --> 01:28:10.450
Thanks, she'd love that.

1046
01:28:10.740 --> 01:28:12.240
- Good day.
- Good day.


1047
01:28:17.280 --> 01:28:18.820
It's kind of surreal.

1048
01:28:18.990 --> 01:28:19.950
Is it?

1049
01:28:20.240 --> 01:28:21.490
How old's your kid?

1050
01:28:21.780 --> 01:28:24.990
I've got a son who's 16,
and a daughter who's14.


1051
01:28:25.160 --> 01:28:26.870
- Really.
- Yup.


1052
01:28:27.530 --> 01:28:29.450
- Incredible.
- It's not.


1053
01:28:30.410 --> 01:28:31.320
Here we are.

1054
01:28:31.490 --> 01:28:33.620
Wow.

1055
01:28:43.740 --> 01:28:44.740
"Kobayashi."

1056
01:28:52.870 --> 01:28:53.870
Come in.

1057
01:29:01.660 --> 01:29:03.450
Put your bag anywhere.

1058
01:29:06.160 --> 01:29:07.870
Your partner...

1059
01:29:08.990 --> 01:29:10.490
What's his job?

1060
01:29:10.870 --> 01:29:14.370
He's an R&D in a pharmaceutical company.

1061
01:29:14.620 --> 01:29:15.740
Makes sense.

1062
01:29:15.910 --> 01:29:17.990
- What does?
- Nothing.


1063
01:29:18.620 --> 01:29:19.700
Any affects?

1064
01:29:20.160 --> 01:29:21.620
Of the virus?

1065
01:29:22.410 --> 01:29:27.320
His research data got leaked,
but so did other companies.


1066
01:29:28.160 --> 01:29:32.570
All he needs for work is the
microscope, so we're fine.


1067
01:29:32.740 --> 01:29:33.740
I see.

1068
01:29:34.490 --> 01:29:36.070
What'd you do today?

1069
01:29:36.740 --> 01:29:39.740
- I had a tea class.
- Really?


1070
01:29:39.990 --> 01:29:40.740
What?

1071
01:29:41.280 --> 01:29:46.870
Sort of unexpected, but I bet
you're cut out for tea ceremonies.


1072
01:29:47.530 --> 01:29:48.570
Thanks.

1073
01:29:48.910 --> 01:29:51.370
But I'm making normal tea for now.

1074
01:29:51.530 --> 01:29:53.490
I'm fine with it.

1075
01:29:55.620 --> 01:29:58.490
Want sweet bean jelly? I froze it.

1076
01:29:58.660 --> 01:30:01.240
- It's top-notch.
- You don't mind?


1077
01:30:01.620 --> 01:30:04.620
My family doesn't like it as I do.

1078
01:30:04.780 --> 01:30:06.120
What a waste.

1079
01:30:06.990 --> 01:30:09.070
Can I help?

1080
01:30:09.240 --> 01:30:11.240
It's okay. Just relax.

1081
01:30:17.990 --> 01:30:20.320
- Don't touch it!
- Sorry.


1082
01:30:21.030 --> 01:30:21.870
I'm sorry.

1083
01:30:24.280 --> 01:30:25.950
Is your kid a fan?

1084
01:30:26.160 --> 01:30:27.700
Yeah, my son is.

1085
01:30:27.910 --> 01:30:28.950
I see.

1086
01:30:29.120 --> 01:30:30.620
I'm embarrassed.

1087
01:30:31.160 --> 01:30:33.740
But anime these days are intriguing.

1088
01:30:33.910 --> 01:30:36.740
Today's package is
a Blu-ray for an anime.


1089
01:30:37.530 --> 01:30:41.370
Because all the VOD services
don't work anymore.


1090
01:30:41.660 --> 01:30:44.740
I missed the package two days ago.

1091
01:30:45.030 --> 01:30:47.570
My son gets cranky, you know?

1092
01:30:47.740 --> 01:30:49.200
Do you watch it too?

1093
01:30:49.370 --> 01:30:51.200
No. Do you?

1094
01:30:51.370 --> 01:30:53.990
I binge watch to kill time now.

1095
01:30:55.620 --> 01:31:00.370
I don't get it anymore.
Can't keep up with the conversation.


1096
01:31:00.780 --> 01:31:03.620
- You can, if you watch it.
- Maybe.


1097
01:31:04.240 --> 01:31:05.990
But I'm not interested.

1098
01:31:06.780 --> 01:31:11.240
I don't mind what people like,
but I'm not interested.


1099
01:31:21.780 --> 01:31:23.620
It's my mother-in-law's.

1100
01:31:24.030 --> 01:31:25.740
Oh, really.

1101
01:31:27.780 --> 01:31:29.620
You still play the piano?

1102
01:31:30.410 --> 01:31:31.200
Huh?

1103
01:31:31.870 --> 01:31:32.620
Not at all.

1104
01:31:33.530 --> 01:31:34.700
I see.

1105
01:31:35.240 --> 01:31:38.700
I only play for
my daughter's violin, too.


1106
01:31:41.620 --> 01:31:44.490
You seem to be scared of silence.

1107
01:31:44.910 --> 01:31:45.870
Do I?

1108
01:31:46.160 --> 01:31:52.120
You keep avoiding what's important.
Even though it's been 20 years.


1109
01:31:52.620 --> 01:31:53.870
What's important?

1110
01:31:55.120 --> 01:31:56.950
Are you happy right now?

1111
01:31:58.780 --> 01:31:59.740
Oh...

1112
01:32:01.620 --> 01:32:05.240
It sounds silly to ask
after seeing this house.


1113
01:32:06.410 --> 01:32:08.490
But that's my only question.

1114
01:32:10.410 --> 01:32:12.990
I haven't thought about it.

1115
01:32:13.280 --> 01:32:15.990
You shouldn't have to think.

1116
01:32:21.910 --> 01:32:22.990
I can't say.

1117
01:32:36.160 --> 01:32:39.740
I do my best
to get by every day.

1118
01:32:40.280 --> 01:32:44.990
There were hard times,
but I wasn't miserable.


1119
01:32:45.910 --> 01:32:49.570
Objectively speaking,
I must be very happy.


1120
01:32:51.030 --> 01:32:56.820
I feel I'd get scolded
if I say I'm not happy.


1121
01:32:57.660 --> 01:33:00.240
I'm asking what you think.

1122
01:33:02.660 --> 01:33:03.870
I don't know...

1123
01:33:10.780 --> 01:33:12.740
Are you happy?

1124
01:33:14.030 --> 01:33:15.700
I'm not.

1125
01:33:15.870 --> 01:33:18.490
Why? Because of your job?

1126
01:33:18.910 --> 01:33:19.820
No.

1127
01:33:21.280 --> 01:33:27.700
Because I've been regretting
not fighting for my feelings.


1128
01:33:28.740 --> 01:33:33.240
I shouldn't have given up,
even if the result was the same.


1129
01:33:33.780 --> 01:33:35.700
But I was ignorant then.

1130
01:33:36.160 --> 01:33:38.490
I was scared to be hurt more.

1131
01:33:39.030 --> 01:33:41.870
That's why I came here to see you.

1132
01:33:42.030 --> 01:33:42.950
Hold on.

1133
01:33:48.030 --> 01:33:53.120
Let me clarify 'cause this conversation
seems important to you.


1134
01:33:53.660 --> 01:33:54.490
What?

1135
01:33:55.910 --> 01:34:00.950
To be honest,
I can't remember your name.


1136
01:34:02.280 --> 01:34:04.200
Are you serious?

1137
01:34:04.410 --> 01:34:09.200
I'm sorry. I hoped I'd recall,
or you'd say it as we talked.


1138
01:34:10.280 --> 01:34:12.620
How could you forget?

1139
01:34:13.410 --> 01:34:15.320
Then it made me wonder.

1140
01:34:15.910 --> 01:34:16.820
What?

1141
01:34:17.160 --> 01:34:19.820
Do you know my name?

1142
01:34:20.410 --> 01:34:21.990
Of course, I do.

1143
01:34:22.240 --> 01:34:24.200
Then who am I?

1144
01:34:26.530 --> 01:34:27.990
Mika Yuki.

1145
01:34:28.160 --> 01:34:29.120
Oh...

1146
01:34:30.910 --> 01:34:31.990
Aya Kobayashi.

1147
01:34:35.620 --> 01:34:37.870
My name's Aya Kobayashi.

1148
01:34:42.280 --> 01:34:46.490
My maiden name's Nomura.
I'm not Mika Yuki either way.


1149
01:34:47.620 --> 01:34:49.700
- You're not Mika?
- No.


1150
01:34:50.160 --> 01:34:53.740
I'm Aya Kobayashi,
and not your classmate.


1151
01:34:54.160 --> 01:34:56.490
You got the wrong person.

1152
01:34:57.410 --> 01:35:01.620
But...you remembered me.

1153
01:35:02.490 --> 01:35:03.820
Well...

1154
01:35:07.660 --> 01:35:10.200
We met on the escalator, right?

1155
01:35:10.660 --> 01:35:11.490
Yeah.

1156
01:35:13.160 --> 01:35:18.990
When we passed each other,
you looked at me all surprised.


1157
01:35:20.490 --> 01:35:25.200
So I thought you
must be someone I know.

1158
01:35:25.780 --> 01:35:31.070
When I went back up, you came down,
and I panicked.


1159
01:35:31.530 --> 01:35:35.240
I was trying hard to recollect.
Then it hit me.


1160
01:35:36.280 --> 01:35:40.200
"She's my classmate
that went to Tokyo for college."


1161
01:35:40.490 --> 01:35:43.370
Doesn't that mean you know me?

1162
01:35:43.620 --> 01:35:45.370
Where's your school?

1163
01:35:45.780 --> 01:35:47.370
Miyagi Girls' High.

1164
01:35:47.910 --> 01:35:49.620
I went to Sendai High.

1165
01:35:53.660 --> 01:35:58.870
See? I'm sorry, it was my mistake.

1166
01:35:59.530 --> 01:36:01.990
I mean, <i>our</i> mistake.

1167
01:36:03.160 --> 01:36:05.370
I don't believe this...

1168
01:36:06.410 --> 01:36:10.950
You must've wanted to see her badly.

1169
01:36:13.160 --> 01:36:15.700
Yes, that's right.

1170
01:36:17.740 --> 01:36:19.450
I missed her so much.

1171
01:36:20.910 --> 01:36:27.240
That must be why you mistook me,
with similar age, for Mika.


1172
01:36:29.910 --> 01:36:31.620
That can't be.

1173
01:36:32.530 --> 01:36:34.950
But you haven't seen her 20 years.

1174
01:36:39.530 --> 01:36:41.450
Did you keep in touch?

1175
01:36:42.490 --> 01:36:43.570
No.

1176
01:36:45.030 --> 01:36:48.240
Cause I heard
she married after college.


1177
01:36:50.740 --> 01:36:54.570
Could it be that
you and Mika were lovers?


1178
01:37:04.160 --> 01:37:05.120
I'm sorry.

1179
01:37:10.780 --> 01:37:11.950
Whoa, excuse me.

1180
01:37:12.120 --> 01:37:14.120
I brought your package.

1181
01:37:15.910 --> 01:37:16.990
Thank you.

1182
01:37:17.280 --> 01:37:19.370
Please sign here.

1183
01:37:19.530 --> 01:37:20.570
Sure.

1184
01:37:24.660 --> 01:37:25.870
<i>Kobayashi</i>

1185
01:37:27.120 --> 01:37:29.570
- Here you go.
- Thank you.


1186
01:37:40.280 --> 01:37:42.240
Why don't you stay longer?

1187
01:37:43.370 --> 01:37:46.370
The sweet bean jelly and kettle's ready.

1188
01:38:37.160 --> 01:38:39.620
It's like a sweet bean popsicle!

1189
01:38:39.780 --> 01:38:40.620
Right?

1190
01:38:41.530 --> 01:38:43.450
A high-grade version.

1191
01:38:49.160 --> 01:38:51.490
Are you sure you're not Mika?

1192
01:38:52.160 --> 01:38:54.620
I'm not Mika. Sorry.

1193
01:38:55.490 --> 01:38:57.620
Ugh.

1194
01:39:03.490 --> 01:39:05.950
Was Mika your first love?

1195
01:39:08.370 --> 01:39:10.320
I'm not sure about that.

1196
01:39:11.370 --> 01:39:13.490
But she was my first partner.

1197
01:39:17.910 --> 01:39:20.240
We dated at the end of high school

1198
01:39:20.530 --> 01:39:24.120
and did long-distance
after I moved to Tokyo.


1199
01:39:24.370 --> 01:39:26.990
Then, she got a boyfriend.

1200
01:39:27.370 --> 01:39:28.240
Oh...

1201
01:39:29.530 --> 01:39:33.370
She wasn't like me,
so I should've seen it coming.


1202
01:39:33.910 --> 01:39:36.490
But I was oblivious somehow.

1203
01:39:36.740 --> 01:39:40.990
You mean, only you
were a genuine lesbian?


1204
01:39:41.160 --> 01:39:42.240
Genuine?

1205
01:39:43.410 --> 01:39:44.320
Yeah.

1206
01:39:45.740 --> 01:39:51.490
We were planning to live together
in Tokyo after college.


1207
01:39:52.120 --> 01:39:55.870
But broke up when she cheated...
I mean, changed.


1208
01:39:56.660 --> 01:39:57.620
I see.

1209
01:39:58.780 --> 01:39:59.990
Never saw her again?

1210
01:40:00.240 --> 01:40:04.370
Yeah. Afterward, someone
told me she married the guy.


1211
01:40:05.530 --> 01:40:07.450
Did you love her?

1212
01:40:19.160 --> 01:40:20.240
My husband...

1213
01:40:23.120 --> 01:40:25.950
He was contacting his high school ex.

1214
01:40:26.120 --> 01:40:27.120
Really?

1215
01:40:29.120 --> 01:40:34.370
I found out because the virus
sent his emails to me.


1216
01:40:35.780 --> 01:40:40.240
You know, you can see
the history of their responses.


1217
01:40:40.410 --> 01:40:41.240
Yeah.

1218
01:40:42.990 --> 01:40:49.740
He wrote in the email, "I really
want to see you, but we shouldn't."


1219
01:40:51.030 --> 01:40:53.990
"I know we love our families."

1220
01:40:54.410 --> 01:40:55.490
He's faithful.

1221
01:40:56.490 --> 01:40:57.450
He is.

1222
01:40:57.870 --> 01:40:59.320
How did you feel?

1223
01:41:02.370 --> 01:41:06.240
It's hard to put it into words.

1224
01:41:07.660 --> 01:41:10.200
But it was beautifully written.

1225
01:41:11.870 --> 01:41:13.870
I was surprised by his words.

1226
01:41:14.280 --> 01:41:15.240
What words?

1227
01:41:21.490 --> 01:41:27.240
"The things you said to me
keeps me going even now."


1228
01:41:30.370 --> 01:41:35.740
"Your existence is my anchor,
even to this day."


1229
01:41:37.240 --> 01:41:43.700
"Meeting you was one of the best things
that has ever happened in my life."


1230
01:41:44.160 --> 01:41:45.490
Wow.

1231
01:41:47.240 --> 01:41:48.740
I kept rereading it.

1232
01:41:50.120 --> 01:41:53.490
But isn't there only one "best thing"?

1233
01:41:53.990 --> 01:41:56.740
Yeah, it's a weird expression.

1234
01:41:57.030 --> 01:41:59.570
Did you tell him you read it?

1235
01:42:00.030 --> 01:42:00.990
No.

1236
01:42:01.280 --> 01:42:04.870
Did your partner...
I mean, Mr. Husband notice?


1237
01:42:05.030 --> 01:42:06.200
"Mr. Husband"?

1238
01:42:07.910 --> 01:42:11.950
I'm not sure.
I think he was too busy back then.


1239
01:42:12.530 --> 01:42:16.450
Almost everything was leaked.

1240
01:42:17.030 --> 01:42:20.320
I bet he couldn't tell what got exposed.

1241
01:42:22.410 --> 01:42:23.870
Not gonna tell him?

1242
01:42:25.660 --> 01:42:28.870
It'll only make things awkward.

1243
01:42:31.280 --> 01:42:34.870
He did contact her, after all.

1244
01:42:36.120 --> 01:42:38.950
And wanted to see her.

1245
01:42:39.410 --> 01:42:40.740
Can't forgive him?

1246
01:42:42.620 --> 01:42:44.240
For just the thought?

1247
01:42:50.990 --> 01:42:55.370
I think you can't stop
wanting to see someone.


1248
01:42:55.780 --> 01:42:58.620
You don't have to be so understanding.

1249
01:43:02.410 --> 01:43:05.950
Sorry. I don't even know you.

1250
01:43:07.910 --> 01:43:08.870
It's okay.

1251
01:43:12.620 --> 01:43:15.070
Do I look understanding?

1252
01:43:21.870 --> 01:43:22.740
What's wrong?

1253
01:43:23.620 --> 01:43:25.820
I keep seeing Mika in you.

1254
01:43:27.280 --> 01:43:29.370
Do I resemble her that much?

1255
01:43:29.620 --> 01:43:32.740
Maybe it's the vibe you give off.

1256
01:43:33.530 --> 01:43:38.240
You look exactly like
what I imagined she'd look now.


1257
01:43:38.490 --> 01:43:40.870
Was Mika understanding?

1258
01:43:41.030 --> 01:43:42.120
Not at all.

1259
01:43:43.870 --> 01:43:48.070
She looks it,
but you can't reason with her.


1260
01:43:48.370 --> 01:43:50.450
Maybe she's really like me.

1261
01:43:58.120 --> 01:44:01.120
I can play Mika if you'd like.

1262
01:44:01.660 --> 01:44:02.740
Play her?

1263
01:44:04.160 --> 01:44:07.370
It seems like a waste.

1264
01:44:07.530 --> 01:44:08.620
Of what?

1265
01:44:08.870 --> 01:44:10.740
The dramatic meeting.

1266
01:44:11.490 --> 01:44:12.950
What do you mean?

1267
01:44:13.160 --> 01:44:15.740
My looks and personality seem to fit.

1268
01:44:15.910 --> 01:44:19.490
- That's not the point.
- I may not be good enough.


1269
01:44:20.780 --> 01:44:26.370
But I know it's something
that means a lot to you.


1270
01:44:32.910 --> 01:44:36.450
I know it's late,
but can I ask your name?


1271
01:44:40.910 --> 01:44:42.320
Natsuko Higuchi.

1272
01:44:43.620 --> 01:44:45.620
Natsuko means "summer child."

1273
01:44:46.530 --> 01:44:47.490
Natsuko.

1274
01:44:48.280 --> 01:44:49.370
Lovely name.

1275
01:45:00.370 --> 01:45:01.490
Natsuko...

1276
01:45:02.530 --> 01:45:04.990
You said you weren't happy.

1277
01:45:06.490 --> 01:45:09.740
Is it my fault?

1278
01:45:10.240 --> 01:45:12.820
Stop it...

1279
01:45:14.530 --> 01:45:17.740
You didn't date anyone after me?

1280
01:45:19.280 --> 01:45:20.820
There were some.

1281
01:45:21.990 --> 01:45:24.070
But I couldn't truly connect.

1282
01:45:24.280 --> 01:45:26.870
Were you truly connected with me?

1283
01:45:31.870 --> 01:45:32.990
Are you mad?

1284
01:45:35.370 --> 01:45:36.120
Yeah.

1285
01:45:39.740 --> 01:45:40.870
I'm mad.

1286
01:45:44.530 --> 01:45:45.700
I'm sorry.

1287
01:45:48.120 --> 01:45:49.450
Don't be.

1288
01:45:50.490 --> 01:45:51.870
It's not you.

1289
01:45:53.120 --> 01:45:56.370
I'm mad I didn't say
the things I should've.


1290
01:45:58.660 --> 01:46:00.240
Like what?

1291
01:46:01.410 --> 01:46:02.820
What I couldn't say.

1292
01:46:04.660 --> 01:46:10.740
When you gave me your last call,
I was at Shibuya Center-gai.


1293
01:46:11.530 --> 01:46:16.870
The trending song and
deeply tanned girls were real noisy.


1294
01:46:19.780 --> 01:46:23.990
But I could hear your voice clearly.

1295
01:46:25.030 --> 01:46:27.740
You sounded determined.

1296
01:46:28.990 --> 01:46:34.240
I sensed you had suffered enough
before you made the call.


1297
01:46:35.280 --> 01:46:38.490
So, I couldn't say anything.

1298
01:46:39.660 --> 01:46:44.320
I knew if I did, it would only
make you suffer more.


1299
01:46:45.530 --> 01:46:50.370
That's why I hung up
and never called again.


1300
01:46:52.530 --> 01:46:55.070
But I wanted to say was

1301
01:46:56.030 --> 01:46:59.620
you're my one and only love.

1302
01:47:05.120 --> 01:47:08.070
You may be able to love someone else,

1303
01:47:08.870 --> 01:47:11.120
but I can't love anyone else.

1304
01:47:14.530 --> 01:47:20.120
Being together with me
may complicate your life.


1305
01:47:21.160 --> 01:47:23.820
But I wanted you to choose me.

1306
01:47:25.030 --> 01:47:26.740
I couldn't say that.

1307
01:47:28.160 --> 01:47:28.990
I see.

1308
01:47:30.660 --> 01:47:36.490
But I didn't come here because
I wanted something from you.


1309
01:47:37.740 --> 01:47:42.620
I just wanted to tell you
that I couldn't say those words.


1310
01:47:43.910 --> 01:47:47.450
Even if it made you suffer,
I should've said it.


1311
01:47:48.240 --> 01:47:53.070
I know now, the pain
was essential for our lives.


1312
01:47:54.280 --> 01:48:01.240
I assumed you'd have a hole
in your life now, just like me.


1313
01:48:02.490 --> 01:48:03.570
So I came.

1314
01:48:05.280 --> 01:48:06.240
A hole?

1315
01:48:08.280 --> 01:48:12.990
You must have a hole
that nothing can fill in.


1316
01:48:16.780 --> 01:48:19.370
There's no way for me to fill it.

1317
01:48:20.740 --> 01:48:23.490
But I have the same hole as you.

1318
01:48:24.490 --> 01:48:30.070
We may be still connected
through that hole.


1319
01:48:31.410 --> 01:48:33.240
I came to tell you that.

1320
01:48:45.660 --> 01:48:46.570
I'm home.

1321
01:48:53.240 --> 01:48:53.990
Is it here?

1322
01:49:02.910 --> 01:49:04.070
Say hello.

1323
01:49:05.160 --> 01:49:05.950
Hello.

1324
01:49:06.660 --> 01:49:08.070
Nice to meet you.

1325
01:49:18.530 --> 01:49:19.700
He's handsome.

1326
01:49:21.780 --> 01:49:23.870
I thought he'd be a geek.

1327
01:49:25.160 --> 01:49:28.490
He can't even say hello.

1328
01:49:31.990 --> 01:49:33.320
I should be going.

1329
01:49:33.530 --> 01:49:36.120
It's okay. He won't come down.

1330
01:49:36.620 --> 01:49:39.620
Your daughter will be back. I'm going.

1331
01:49:40.120 --> 01:49:43.620
Okay. Can I walk you to the station?

1332
01:49:44.370 --> 01:49:46.620
Yeah. Thanks.

1333
01:49:50.530 --> 01:49:55.450
Kei, I'm going to walk
my friend to the station.


1334
01:50:09.120 --> 01:50:11.740
So your son's name is Kei.

1335
01:50:12.030 --> 01:50:12.950
Yeah.

1336
01:50:13.490 --> 01:50:14.740
And the girl's Yu.

1337
01:50:14.990 --> 01:50:15.740
Right.

1338
01:50:16.910 --> 01:50:17.990
How'd you know?

1339
01:50:18.160 --> 01:50:19.870
You mentioned it.

1340
01:50:20.280 --> 01:50:21.320
Oh, yeah.

1341
01:50:21.910 --> 01:50:24.200
Yu means "to play."

1342
01:50:24.780 --> 01:50:26.200
Nice, simple names.

1343
01:50:26.410 --> 01:50:32.870
We wanted gender-neutral names
so it wouldn't shackle them later.


1344
01:50:33.030 --> 01:50:34.620
You're progressive.

1345
01:50:35.780 --> 01:50:37.620
What's Mr. Husband like?

1346
01:50:40.660 --> 01:50:43.490
He's a steady, diligent person.

1347
01:50:44.030 --> 01:50:45.990
That might be the best.

1348
01:50:46.160 --> 01:50:49.120
- You think so?
- Well, I don't know him.


1349
01:50:49.280 --> 01:50:53.490
But I felt trust and a little distance
from your tone.


1350
01:50:54.910 --> 01:50:55.990
You're right.

1351
01:50:57.030 --> 01:50:59.490
- But you missed "love."
- Sorry.


1352
01:50:59.910 --> 01:51:00.820
It's okay.

1353
01:51:02.240 --> 01:51:04.490
I've never told anyone before.

1354
01:51:05.120 --> 01:51:06.370
I'm honored.

1355
01:51:07.410 --> 01:51:08.700
I'm amazed.

1356
01:51:18.910 --> 01:51:19.700
What is it?

1357
01:51:20.240 --> 01:51:23.370
Who did you mistake me for?

1358
01:51:24.620 --> 01:51:28.370
She was my high school classmate.
A boyish girl.


1359
01:51:28.660 --> 01:51:30.320
Were you two close?

1360
01:51:30.530 --> 01:51:34.620
Not really. We weren't that close.

1361
01:51:36.160 --> 01:51:40.370
She often played the piano
alone at lunch break.


1362
01:51:40.780 --> 01:51:44.490
I also played the piano as a hobby.

1363
01:51:45.160 --> 01:51:48.740
So we started meeting
in the music room at lunch.


1364
01:51:49.620 --> 01:51:54.120
We took turns playing the piano
during lunch break


1365
01:51:54.660 --> 01:51:57.740
and ate listening to each other's piano.

1366
01:51:58.660 --> 01:52:03.120
We didn't talk in class.
Only in the music room.


1367
01:52:03.280 --> 01:52:05.570
- What a lovely memory.
- Yeah.


1368
01:52:06.030 --> 01:52:07.820
It was sort of special.

1369
01:52:08.780 --> 01:52:11.620
We lost contact after she went to Tokyo.

1370
01:52:15.160 --> 01:52:22.120
<i>Sendai Station</i>

1371
01:52:23.780 --> 01:52:24.620
Hey.

1372
01:52:26.280 --> 01:52:28.370
Let's play pretend again.

1373
01:52:29.370 --> 01:52:30.950
Where should we start?

1374
01:52:31.120 --> 01:52:35.450
I'll be your boyish pianist this time.

1375
01:52:35.660 --> 01:52:37.370
But my memory's hazy.

1376
01:52:37.530 --> 01:52:39.990
- It seems unfair.
- Why?


1377
01:52:40.160 --> 01:52:41.200
Let me do it!

1378
01:52:43.030 --> 01:52:45.240
All right. You walk from there.

1379
01:52:45.410 --> 01:52:48.950
We meet when I come up
the escalator, okay?


1380
01:52:49.120 --> 01:52:50.240
It's like a skit.

1381
01:53:28.660 --> 01:53:29.490
Aya?

1382
01:53:31.410 --> 01:53:32.620
Is it you?

1383
01:53:34.620 --> 01:53:36.820
Do you recognize me?

1384
01:53:37.410 --> 01:53:39.320
Yeah, from high school.

1385
01:53:40.160 --> 01:53:42.620
But I can't remember your name.

1386
01:53:42.780 --> 01:53:44.320
It doesn't matter.

1387
01:53:44.910 --> 01:53:47.620
Remember playing the piano together?

1388
01:53:47.780 --> 01:53:48.700
Of course.

1389
01:53:49.240 --> 01:53:51.700
Why are you back from Tokyo?

1390
01:53:52.530 --> 01:53:55.490
For the reunion. 
I'm on my way back.

1391
01:53:55.660 --> 01:53:58.240
Why were you invited, but not me?

1392
01:53:58.410 --> 01:54:00.240
Who knows?

1393
01:54:01.240 --> 01:54:05.990
But I'm glad to see you.
I was wondering how you were doing.


1394
01:54:06.370 --> 01:54:07.370
You mean it?

1395
01:54:08.120 --> 01:54:08.990
I do.

1396
01:54:09.410 --> 01:54:14.490
I'm glad. I thought no one from
high school would remember me.


1397
01:54:14.660 --> 01:54:19.240
No way. I was secretly proud
that I could talk with you.


1398
01:54:19.620 --> 01:54:21.200
- You were?
- Yeah.


1399
01:54:21.870 --> 01:54:27.120
You gave off an antisocial vibe,
but many wanted to talk to you.


1400
01:54:27.620 --> 01:54:29.370
- Are you sure?
- I am.


1401
01:54:29.740 --> 01:54:31.370
You were admired.

1402
01:54:31.660 --> 01:54:34.490
Cut it out. You're gonna make me cry.

1403
01:54:37.780 --> 01:54:39.070
How are you doing?

1404
01:54:39.240 --> 01:54:44.120
Good. There are struggles,
but I live every day to the fullest.


1405
01:54:44.410 --> 01:54:47.620
I'm so glad you haven't changed.

1406
01:54:48.160 --> 01:54:50.070
And you? Are you good?

1407
01:54:51.780 --> 01:54:55.570
I can't answer straight away like you.

1408
01:54:55.780 --> 01:54:57.120
You're not well?

1409
01:54:57.490 --> 01:54:59.370
- My body's fine.
- Then...


1410
01:55:00.530 --> 01:55:03.070
It's not a big problem.

1411
01:55:03.990 --> 01:55:08.700
But sometimes I wonder why I'm here.

1412
01:55:12.160 --> 01:55:17.240
I could've become anything,
but time flew past before I knew.


1413
01:55:18.660 --> 01:55:20.240
I'm fairly satisfied.

1414
01:55:21.660 --> 01:55:23.870
This is what I chose.

1415
01:55:24.870 --> 01:55:27.950
And I know it's wrong to want more.

1416
01:55:30.160 --> 01:55:30.990
But...

1417
01:55:35.410 --> 01:55:39.740
I'm not passionate
about anything anymore.


1418
01:55:43.030 --> 01:55:44.870
I don't know what to do.

1419
01:55:46.370 --> 01:55:47.320
Time is...

1420
01:55:48.530 --> 01:55:50.370
slowly killing me.

1421
01:55:58.240 --> 01:56:01.120
I'm sorry to say
this all of a sudden.

1422
01:56:02.160 --> 01:56:02.990
It's okay.

1423
01:56:05.530 --> 01:56:08.620
Can I tell you how
I saw you back then?

1424
01:56:10.030 --> 01:56:10.820
Sure.

1425
01:56:12.160 --> 01:56:16.990
You said everyone admired me,
but that's wrong.


1426
01:56:17.530 --> 01:56:22.990
I always felt different,
like everyone observed me from afar.


1427
01:56:24.410 --> 01:56:27.950
I always felt like an outcast.

1428
01:56:29.370 --> 01:56:32.370
You were the only one that stepped in.

1429
01:56:32.910 --> 01:56:36.820
It was just one step,
but it meant a lot to me.


1430
01:56:37.620 --> 01:56:43.320
You were the only light for me.
I could find you anywhere you were.


1431
01:56:46.120 --> 01:56:49.320
Your existence gave me power.

1432
01:56:50.280 --> 01:56:51.240
It's true.

1433
01:56:51.410 --> 01:56:55.370
You have the ability
to give people power.


1434
01:56:55.530 --> 01:56:57.200
Please remember that.

1435
01:56:59.740 --> 01:57:00.490
Thanks.

1436
01:57:02.660 --> 01:57:06.990
But I didn't say <i>everyone</i> admired you.

1437
01:57:07.280 --> 01:57:08.070
Huh?

1438
01:57:08.660 --> 01:57:10.870
I admired you.

1439
01:57:17.990 --> 01:57:18.950
Thank you.

1440
01:57:23.030 --> 01:57:24.620
I'm glad I met you.

1441
01:57:26.280 --> 01:57:28.950
I'm glad I met you, too.

1442
01:57:33.160 --> 01:57:33.870
Bye.

1443
01:57:35.280 --> 01:57:36.070
See you!

1444
01:57:37.660 --> 01:57:38.370
See you.

1445
01:58:52.780 --> 01:58:54.120
- Wait.
- What's wrong?


1446
01:58:55.780 --> 01:58:58.370
- It's nothing big.
- What is it?


1447
01:58:58.990 --> 01:59:01.240
But I can only tell you.

1448
01:59:01.410 --> 01:59:02.740
Tell me anything.

1449
01:59:03.410 --> 01:59:05.240
- I remembered.
- What?


1450
01:59:05.410 --> 01:59:06.370
Her name.

1451
01:59:08.620 --> 01:59:09.990
It's Nozomi.

1452
01:59:10.740 --> 01:59:11.700
Nozomi?

1453
01:59:14.370 --> 01:59:16.070
- Nozomi!
- Nozomi!


1454
01:59:19.410 --> 01:59:20.370
And her surname?

1455
01:59:20.780 --> 01:59:21.990
Can't remember.

